args:
Cleo and Lathna learn from the woman in the
cave that she performed a heretical ritual, and
are relieved to have identified the true culprit.
However, the moment Lathna touches her, the
woman transforms into Nyarlathotep. Lathna
despairs, believing that she has killed her.
That's the last of the zombies dealt with.\nI must say, I did not expect to find a place\nlike this in the cave depths.
It is suspicious, to say the least.\nPerhaps this is our suspect's hideaway.
I dunno, but there are strange letters\nand pictures all over the place.
...That's a rather unsettling magic circle.\nI feel as though I've seen this pattern\nsomewhere before...
Ah, right! It's the same sort as what we\nsaw with Curran and the others in that\nheretical library they were investigating.
I'm okay... I, um, just tripped.\nIs this...a book?

Day OO, Month of the Lovely Dragon
It's been a few days since I lost my husband.
I still can't believe it. This is a nightmare.
Why can't I wake up? I've never felt so lonely.
Day XX, Month of the Wardragon\nI long to see him. My heart is broken.\nO God, please return him to me! Please!

Day ZZ, Month of the Raindragon
Voice. Voice. Voice. Guidance. Yes.
I hear it, the Revival, it whispers.
The lanterns, lanterns, LANTERNS!
Ritual will happen on day of the lanterns.

Day OX, Month of the Blazewyrm
The music, the flesh, the feast, sacrifice.
The lanterns, they come! COME COME COME!
O God, O Ancient One, thy name is...
It's a diary. It looks like it belongs to the\nwoman—poor deceased Banquo's wife.
The entries get increasingly nonsensical\nthe more you read. What in the world...?
Was that a scream?\nIt came from beyond that gate!
Nnngh... It's no good. The gate won't open.\nSomething's preventing us!
Who is that? And...wait.\nTheir body—it's transparent!
Oh! The gate, it's opening! C-could that\nhave been the ghost of the man who died?
This isn't the time to be thinking about\nthat. We have to hurry on.
The woman! She's still breathing. Good.\nMy healing magic should prove effective.
Thank goodness you're awake! Are you\nall right? Can you remember anything?
I... That's right, I...wanted to see my\nhusband, so I tried the revival ritual...
The one you mentioned in your diary?

Yes... A strange voice told me about it.
It said that if I drew magic circles on the
lanterns to make them go up the river,
my husband would be revived.
So it was your work after all.\nBut why were you incapacitated here?
I don't know. In order to bring my husband\nback, I called to all of the souls sleeping\nin this land, but...
It proved too much for me to handle.\nI could not find my husband's soul, and\nthe wailing of the others ate away at me.
I become someone not myself!\nI was transformed! Yes...and then...\nI couldn't bear it!
From inside a distant consciousness, a\nvoice spoke. It told me that I was not\nstrong enough to be the Emissary.
I remember nothing after that.\nI can't hear the voice...\nThe voice... The voice... My guide...
Ma'am? ...I don't think we'll be able to get\nany more out of her.
At least now we know who was responsible\nfor the incident.
Yeah. So this lady did the ritual and\nmade the lanterns go backwards... Right?
Yes. She is some manner of heretic, and\nmisused the lanterns in a bid to revive\nher husband through dark magicks.
But this was a Hinomotoan festival. How\nwould that work for a heretical ritual?

It's said that sometimes, Hinomoto's
lanterns contain remnants of the deceased,
like locks of hair, in order to guide the
prayers sent after them.
Likely that unwittingly made them perfect\nbeacons to use in summoning back the\nsouls of the dead.
So she used the festival to do her\nritual, but it...failed, somehow?

Yes. She did manage to reverse the
lanterns, but she could not control the
mass of souls she summoned, and ended
up collapsing.
And then the souls that had broken free\nfrom her grasp reacted to your power and\nturned into zombies.
Why zombies? Is it because I really am\na bad person, so the souls turned into\nsomething bad, too?

No, I don't think that's it. Likely the
remains in the lanterns and the souls
were fused when they came into
unexpected contact with your power.
Merely an accident caused by your power\ndistorting the original purpose of the\nmagic circles.
So it wasn't that something inside me\nwas trying to summon the zombies...?
Right. Meaning you were not responsible\nfor the incident. We know that much now.
So don't you spend another second\nthinking about how things would be\nbetter off if you weren't here! Okay?
Right. I'm...not a bad girl after all, huh?
Of course not. And once we sort out\nthe zombies, we'll have this whole\nmatter wrapped up nicely.
Yeah... Then first, maybe she can tell us\nhow to get the souls to go back to where\nthey came from...
Thus is the chaos of glittering stars poured\ninto the closed casket, and the unripened\nvessel is released from its long sleep!

The time has come. We are Chaos. We
are without Beginning nor End. We are the
Dawn and Dusk. An unwaking nightmare
on bleakest, blackest morn comes.
The time of Our awakening is nigh.\nWe are...
N Y A R L A T H O T E P
It can't be. The woman—she\nturned into Nyarlathotep...?
Why...? This woman isn't the\nEmissary! This shouldn't—!

With Our brethren's aid, We have been
freed from boundless slumber. She who
woke Us was from the start a thrall of the
Ancient One; one of Our faceless vessels.
No... She's been a part of you all along?\nThen the voice who told her about the\nritual to bring back her husband...

Yes. It was We who imparted to the
woman vessel the means to perform
the rite. And then We had her gather
souls to awaken Us. Yet she was a void.

Brethren, We are grateful for your help.
Our vessel's collapse, Our awakening,
the heretical stride of the walking flesh...
All are your achievements.
You're saying that your awakening was\nhastened by Lathna's power?
It's my fault that this woman...died?

Your power invited us. We are free of our
shackles now because of you, and now
We shall fulfill our duty as Emissary
of the Ancient One.
We go now, to gather sacrifices unto the\naltar of worship.
Stay back! You can't come near me!
It was me who summoned the zombies.\nAnd it was me who killed the woman and\nmade her into Nyarlathotep.
Everything, all of it, it's my fault.\nThat's what Nyarlathotep said.
I'm sorry... I'm so sorry, Cleo.\nI'm not a good girl after all.
And bad girls deserve to be alone.
